%% Mermaid sequence diagram for restore lifecycle
sequenceDiagram
  participant CLI as CLI
  participant DB as MySQL Queue
  participant D as Daemon
  participant S3 as AWS S3
  participant MySQL as MySQL Host

  CLI->>DB: insert job (status=queued)
  D->>DB: poll for queued job
  D->>DB: acquire lock + mark running
  D->>S3: fetch latest backup
  D->>D: verify disk space
  D->>D: extract archive to workspace
  D->>D: cleanup orphaned staging databases
  D->>MySQL: run myloader restore to staging_name
  D->>MySQL: execute post-restore SQL scripts on staging
  D->>MySQL: add pullDB metadata table to staging
  D->>MySQL: atomic rename staging tables to target
  D->>MySQL: drop staging database
  D->>DB: mark complete + append events
  CLI->>DB: status query
  DB-->>CLI: job status = complete
